rows.label: tev066201_SEL1041
rows.name: Ask De Sazon about recent developments.

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0001
rows.name:
I cannot tell you anything about us without Prince
Jiarg's leave.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0002
rows.name:
Though of course I expect there will be no more trouble
between us.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0007
rows.name: Leaving Ganglion has only left us more impoverished.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0008
rows.name:
We struggle to find even enough food to eat.
But it is better this way.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0009
rows.name:
I would rather starve with my Wrothian pride intact
than dirty my hands for those fiends another day.
This is a life better lived![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0010
rows.name:
Wherever Prince Jiarg goes, we shall follow—
even into the depths of hell![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0015
rows.name:
The prince is the last surviving member of the Wrothian
royal line, and chief of our band of mercenaries.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0016
rows.name: He is a just man who always puts his people first.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0017
rows.name: I would die for him should he ask it.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0018
rows.name:
I wonder if you can say the same.
Would you give your life for your BLADE leader?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0023
rows.name:
Some went to honor their word, and others to sate
their desires—but there is no mistake that many of my
people have gone to New LA.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0024
rows.name:
But my house stays with Prince Jiarg.
No hunger or danger could drive us from his side.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0025
rows.name:
My pride and obligation is to keep him safe.
All else matters not.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0026
rows.name: My wife De Soghu understands.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG0027
rows.name:
As for my son, if he is a proper Wrothian,
then my feelings will one day be his as well.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG1001
rows.name:
Ezich has left this land and abandoned his duty to
protect Prince Jiarg.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG1002
rows.name: He is no son to me. I have no son![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG1003
rows.name:
I ask you, is freedom wondrous enough a prize to
slight one's fellows and cast aside one's own family?
Pah! A pox on him![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG1008
rows.name:
I thank you for your help before, proud warrior!
With your aid, we were able to stop my son from
pursuing his madness.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG1009
rows.name:
I will keep whipping his body and mind into shape
until he learns how a true Wrothian is meant to live![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG1010
rows.name:
One must be prepared to die if the prince says "die,"
and kill if the prince says "kill." There is no other way.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev066201_MSG1011
rows.name:
Ezich is a whelp who does not understand this.
But if it takes months or even years, I will mold him
into a proper Wrothian![ST:wait ]
